doc.after: The education system in the province of Quebec is slightly different from other systems in North America Between the high school and university levels there is an additional college level called CEGEP It is at the same time a preparatory school preparing students for admission to university and a technical school offering courses which lead to technical diplomas and specializations In Montreal seventeen CEGEPs offer courses in French and five in English
